Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 9. Boil a #kettle{}.

Chop the @Potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (peel first if you prefer). Peel the @Garlic Cloves{2}.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} on high heat with @salt{1/2%tsp}. Add the potatoes and half the peeled garlic to the water and cook until just tender, ~{12-14%minutes}.

About ~{5%minutes} before the potatoes are ready, drain the @Fish Pie Mix{1%pack} and add the fish to the pan.

Simmer until the fish is cooked through, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish. It's cooked when opaque in the middle.

Once the potatoes and fish are cooked, drain and allow to steam uncovered for ~{2%minutes}. Return to the pan, off the heat.

Mash the potatoes with a #potato masher{}, ensuring the mixture isn't too smooth so that some small chunks of potato remain.

Stir in the @Korma Curry Paste{50%g}, @Curry Powder Mix{1%sachet}, @Breadcrumbs{50%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp}. Season with @ground black pepper{} and mix together.

Allow the mixture to cool slightly, then shape into 2cm thick patties, 3 per person.

Transfer the fish cakes to a large, lightly oiled #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with oil, then bake on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{24-26%minutes}. Carefully turn halfway through.

== Carrot Salad ==

Trim and peel the @Carrot{1}. Use the #peeler{} to peel long ribbons down the length of the carrot, stopping at the core.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine the @Red Wine Vinegar{12%ml}, a drizzle of @oil{} and @sugar{pinch}. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Add the carrot and toss to coat. Set aside to pickle.

Grate the remaining garlic (or use a #garlic press{}).

In a #small bowl{}, combine the @Mango Chutney{40%g} and @Mayonnaise{1%tbsp}.

== Peas ==

When the fish cakes have ~{5%minutes} remaining, wipe out the (now empty) fish pan and return to medium heat with a drizzle of oil.

Once hot, add the @Peas{120%g} and stir-fry for ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the grated garlic and cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}, then remove from the heat. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

== To Serve ==

When everything's ready, add the @Baby Leaf Mix{20%g} to the carrot bowl. Toss to coat.

> TIP: Don't add the leaves too early or they'll go soggy.

Share the fish cakes between your plates.

Serve the carrot salad and peas alongside. Dollop the mango mayo on the side for dipping to finish. Enjoy!